rComments: Super nice guy, but dry as the sahara.  Not great at explaining concepts in class, but if you ask him questions after class he does a better job
What a dry, dry teacher.  Read off of the power points (which were posted online), required tons of crappy reading, and bored me to death.  Neil Vander Most, my TA, was particularly awful.

If u sit in the front row u'll pick up on his habits (like squeezing an invisible ball/his love 4 acronyms/testing his IR pen a 100 times).1 on 1 he's really helpful 2! Will miss this class!
